{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4baf4756-5fee-4590-8d8c-28900a687b14","content":"No files found in the working directory — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — this tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding}` on this page is validated and compiled against that type at build time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, mistyped or missing properties (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`) become **compiler errors**, not silent runtime failures.\n\nTo ensure this is enforced, confirm your `.csproj` does **not** disable it:\n\n```xml\n<!-- This should NOT be in your .csproj (it disables the feature): -->\n<!-- <MauiXamlCBindingInfoTracking>false</MauiXamlCBindingInfoTracking> -->\n```\n\nThen just build:\n\n```bash\ndotnet build\n```\n\nA typo like `{Binding Themee}` will produce:\n\n```\nerror XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\n## Tips\n\n| Scenario | Approach |\n|---|---|\n| Disable compiled binding for one expression | `{Binding Path=Foo, x:DataType={x:Null}}` |\n| Different type in a `DataTemplate` | Put `x:DataType` on the `DataTemplate` element itself |\n| Nested types (e.g. `ObservableCollection<Item>`) | Set `x:DataType` on the inner template targeting `Item` |\n\nThat's it — the only required change is adding `x:DataType`. The compiler handles the rest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad0bb974-82ce-4784-972a-77f17c56fa35","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking about a conceptual page they have. I'll provide them with the guidance on how to convert their page to use compiled bindings and how to catch binding errors at build time.","outputTokens":662,"requestId":"981D:15979F:158A90A:18146FD:6A051DA8"},"id":"2c031435-ec67-44db-a69b-856d19994f2c","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:22.532Z","parentId":"7db8505e-4f1f-4c7d-95dd-031408371c89"}
